		<title>02 Farming and Land Use.</title>
		<content>  The farmland in Whitburn can be      
 divided into two categories,arable    
 land and permanent pasture.           
  The crops grown on the arable land   
 are wheat,barley,potatoes,turnips,hay 
 and silage.These crops are used in    
 rotation and cover an area of 49.77   
 hectares.                             
  The permanent pasture is used for the
 grazing of the Friesian dairy         
 cattle.Pasture land covers 17.66      
 hectares.                             
  A green belt separates Whitburn from 
 surrounding towns and villages.       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
